    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nEnabled `extui` in combination with `set cursorline cursorlineopt=screenline` and enabled tree-sitter parser can lead to not immediate visual effect of `matchdelete()` Vimscript function. This leads to flickering when its effect is expected to be done immediately (like in \"auto highlight word at cursor\" type of usage).\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Create 'init-auto-match.lua' with the following code:\n\n    <details><summary>init-auto-match.lua code</summary>\n\n    ```lua\n    -- Minimal set of options needed to reproduce the issue (plus later\n    -- tree-sitter parser). Removing any will not reproduce the issue.\n    vim.o.cursorline = true\n    vim.o.cursorlineopt = 'screenline'\n    require('vim._extui').enable({ enable = true })\n\n    -- Auto highlight word at cursor with debounce on cursor movement\n    local timer, cur_match = vim.uv.new_timer(), nil\n\n    -- Highlight word under cursor\n    local add_hl = vim.schedule_wrap(function() cur_match = vim.fn.matchadd('Red', [[\\k*\\%#\\k*]]) end)\n\n    local remove_hl = function() pcall(vim.fn.matchdelete, cur_match) end\n\n    local auto_hl = function()\n      timer:stop()\n      remove_hl()\n      timer:start(500, 0, add_hl)\n    end\n\n    vim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('CursorMoved', { callback = auto_hl })\n    vim.api.nvim_set_hl(0, 'Red', { bg = 'Red' })\n\n    -- Demo buffer that leads to a very high rate of reproducing flickering\n    -- that comes from not immediate `matchdelete` (I presume)\n    -- It sets up a markdown file with enabled tree-sitter\n    vim.defer_fn(function()\n      local buf_id = vim.api.nvim_create_buf(true, false)\n      local lines = {}\n      for _ = 1, 2000 do\n        table.insert(lines, '[](https://github.com/neovim/neovim) - Extensible Vim based editor; it is very good')\n      end\n      vim.api.nvim_buf_set_lines(buf_id, 0, -1, false, lines)\n      vim.api.nvim_set_current_buf(buf_id)\n\n      vim.treesitter.start(buf_id, 'markdown')\n      vim.cmd('normal! MfE')\n    end, 100)\n    ```\n\n    </details>\n2. `nvim --clean -u init-auto-match.lua`\n3. Move around with `w` and `b`.\n\nHere is the demo of the issue (had to record in 60 fps because it is quick, but consistent; visible in real life on almost every jump during this recording):\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/00406fd5-af59-4778-9c1c-4f8ac3729c4d\n\nHere is how it should look (this is recorded without enabling `vim._extui`):\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/1abfed51-b084-44d3-bbac-3fb564e169d7\n\ncc @luukvbaal \n\n### Expected behavior\n\nVisual effects of `matchdelete()` are consistent and do not depend on whether ui2 (or cursorline, or tree-sitter) is enabled.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-1465+ga08aa77e40\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo, doesn't have these capabilities\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nEndeavourOS Linux x86_64, 6.17.1-arch1-1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGhostty 1.2.0-arch1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\nAppimage",
